Older:

Put Inconsolata.otf in ~/.fonts/ :
cd ~/.fonts
wget http://levien.com/type/myfonts/Inconsolata.otf

This seems to be necessary in the account that is running the X client
process (where the program is running) -- it doesn't help that it is
installed in the account that is running the X server (the machine at which
I am sitting).


mkdir -p ~/.fonts
cd ~/.fonts
VER=v3.003
fontfile=Hack-${VER}-ttf.zip
wget https://github.com/source-foundry/Hack/releases/download/${VER}/${fontfile}
unzip ${fontfile}
rm -f ${fontfile}
fc-cache

mkdir -p ~/.fonts
cd ~/.fonts
VER=v1.200
fontfile=monaspace-${VER}.zip
wget https://github.com/githubnext/monaspace/releases/download/${VER}/${fontfile}
unzip ${fontfile}
rm -f ${fontfile}
fc-cache



